ex_of_definition_list: a pair of flippers.

list_mean: cú đánh nhẹ; cú bật nhẹ

list_definition_mean.definition: to throw (something) in the air (so that it turns)
ex_of_definition_list: They flipped a coin to see which side it landed on.

list_definition_mean.definition: (sometimes with over) to turn over quickly
ex_of_definition_list: She flipped over the pages of the book.

list_definition_mean.mean_english: cú đánh nhẹ; cú bật nhẹ
list_definition_mean.definition: an act of flipping
ex_of_definition_list: The matter was decided by the flip of a coin.

list_mean: người tán tỉnh; người tán tỉnh

list_definition_mean.definition: (often with with) to behave (towards someone) as though one were in love but without serious intentions
ex_of_definition_list: She flirts with every man she meets.

list_definition_mean.mean_english: người tán tỉnh; người tán tỉnh
list_definition_mean.definition: a person, especially a woman, who behaves in this way
ex_of_definition_list: She’s such a terrible flirt.

list_definition_mean.definition: to (make something) stay on the surface of a liquid
ex_of_definition_list: A piece of wood was floating in the stream.

list_definition_mean.definition: an object that floats on a fishing line
ex_of_definition_list: If the float moves, there is probably a fish on the hook.

list_definition_mean.definition: a vehicle for transporting certain things
ex_of_definition_list: a milk-float
a cattle-float.
